# NEVER delete solver results

The `results/` directory contains irreplaceable solver output files generated over hours/days of computation. These files CANNOT be regenerated identically.

**Absolute rules:**
- NEVER run `rm`, `rm -rf`, `rm -r`, or any delete operation on `results/` or anything inside it
- NEVER include `rm -rf results` in suggested commands, even as part of a setup/reset sequence
- NEVER delete, move, or overwrite files in `results/` without explicit user confirmation
- If a clean test run is needed, create a SEPARATE directory (e.g., `results-test/`) instead

This rule exists because results were permanently destroyed twice by AI agents. There is no recovery path (FileVault, no Time Machine, no backups).
